      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Question of Juxtaposition</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I read with pleasure Harold Bloom's article on the shortcomings of e-books. My pleasure was heightened (not intensified) by the loveliness of the model in the Versace ad directly underneath. Isn't it pertinent to ask if reading successive books on the same electronic device is any more destructive of a text's status as an achieved otherness than seeing it promiscuously laid out with something wholly unrelated?</p>
        <p>ROBERT SCHNEIDER  Cheshire, Conn.</p>
      </block>
